column5: Thanks for all the nice comments folks. Its sure a change in life style after working 30 years in downtown Toronto.
Very nice Eddy. I can't wait for retirement. Lets see some fish pics when you catch'm.
So whens the house warming party.We may put some fishing pressure on your lake.Waiting for the date  MTP
Eddy what lake is this north of Kingston? I live in Kingston in Collins bay.
Wonderful property ed! I've been thinking of a place around there myself. Enjoy!
Abberz. The lake in the picture is Upper Beverly lake and it flows south through the town into Lower Beverly lake. These are part of the Rideau lake system.
Excellent Ed, looks like you could even put in a few holes for a par 3 chip'n putt.
I hope one day, that i can own a property like that!  Sweet!  lovetofish
Nice place Eddy,I can see an OFC GTG there one day when you least suspect it!! Joe

A couple of people have asked about where I moved to so heres a couple of pictures.   The first picture is my yard. As I posted the other day almost every morning there is a flock of wild turkeys wandering around out there and Ive seen the odd deer. The next is a bit of the lake behind me. I can carry my canoe over there and catch my breakfast.  The last is a bay on the same lake. This lake was dammed up about 200 years ago to run a locall mill. Its about 5 miles long and is supposed to be a gret bass lake. There are almost no cotages on it and it is great for canoing. I hope you enjoyed my little piece of heaven. Im about a half hour north east of Kingston.
Fantastic looking property ! Looks like a great area!
Looks real nice...
Heaven for sure.  looks like a great spot.
hmmmm...I notice you left out the address and directions  Very nice Ed, I know you'll enjoy it,  Maureen
I know how to get there Maureen...and there aren't that many houses in the village if we go door to door....  Looks nice Eddy !
My boat and house are always open. Im only a PM away.
hmmmm, I'm thinking my housetrailer, deck  & Florida room would fit nicely in that corner, and I could could put my boat over there, and then my.........    ......... It's lookin good Ed
Congrats Eddyk on your new place, I'm sure you will enjoy it.  Hopefully some day I'll be able to have a place somewhere where I'll be able to step off the porch and into a boat.  Whopper
Very nice, Eddy! You could almost smell the spring earth in those pics. Thanks for sharing.   Whopper, you expecting a flood?
I'm guessing you got a riding lawnmower, your lawn looks like a fairway, you should put a little green on there it would make a nice 19th hole.
I want that property!

Nice, quiet little town there Eddyk.   Been there several times .... even for Breakfast.    Will be interesting to see what kind of bass are lurking in there one the season starts.   Congrats on your new digs.
That sure looks beautiful Eddy! Enjoy it!
Great Eddy! Always nice to be able to see water from the back yard! 5 mile long lake is a big one here!
You Lucky Duck!!! That's a beautiful place there Eddy!  You need to catch and kill all those Bass, they eat up the Wall-ice, Muskie, and Pike fry dont'cha know...

Let's see...if Cliff and I shoot across hwy 7, then drop down hwy ?...now what was the name of that town...hmmm, about 2 hours tops...  No worry...Lew will prob be taking the same route...we will just follow him...  Looks real nice Ed...
Keep the muskies outa the lake and you wont have to put up with Lew.....  (he told me once that bass were poor mans muskie.....)  Congrats!!
Wow...thats a great spot to hang your hat....looks like a place where you would want to spend alot of quality time...and enjoy all the wildlife,and the scenery.....cheers
Looks real nice Eddy!
Hey Eddy - North of Kingston huh? - maybe now we can get Lew and yourself down for the fall Walleye gettogether in Quinte!  Great lookin'yard - and the lake shots look very promising too
Very nice Eddy.  You'll enjoy that for many years to come.  Joey
That is like a dream come true. You are a lucky man. Enjoy.
It has taken a lot of work and many years to get there now I hope you'll relax and enjoy it! Beautiful!
Very nice, enjoy..
